 :tx/rationale "Create task: CCE-2: Concept entity schema and crystallization engine. CONTEXT: Concepts are the missing primitive — first-class entities representing emergent clusters of meaning. They solve: synonym problem (two tags for same pattern detected via embedding proximity), connection quality (shared concept = connection), agent handoff (seed transmits concepts not raw observations). This IS OBSERVER-6 from the bedrock vision: 'observation clustering → proposed categories.' RATIONALE: Tags are Keyword values with no identity, no relationships, no evolution. Concepts are entities with embeddings, descriptions, membership, evolution. Tags are identifiers without identity. Concepts are living knowledge. APPROACH: (1) Schema additions (schema.rs full_schema_datoms): :concept/name (String, One), :concept/description (String, One), :concept/embedding (Bytes, One — centroid of member embeddings, 1024 bytes for 256 f32), :concept/member-count (Long, One), :concept/created-at (Long, One), :concept/variance (Bytes, One — intra-cluster distance as f64 bytes). Plus Ref attribute: :exploration/concept (Ref, Many — observation → concept membership). (2) Create crates/braid-kernel/src/concept.rs (~400 LOC). Core types: pub struct ConceptSummary { entity: EntityId, name: String, description: String, member_count: usize, embedding: Option<Vec<f32>>, variance: f64 }. Core functions: pub fn find_nearest_concept(store, embedding) -> Option<(EntityId, f32)> — cosine scan of concept centroids, returns best match + similarity. pub fn assign_to_concept(store, observation_entity, observation_embedding) -> ConceptAssignment — returns Joined(concept_entity, similarity) or Uncategorized. JOIN_THRESHOLD = 0.65 (tunable via policy manifest). pub fn crystallize_concepts(store, uncategorized_embeddings) -> Vec<NewConcept> — cluster uncategorized observations (agglomerative clustering, minimum 3 members), create concept entities. Called at harvest time. pub fn concept_inventory(store) -> Vec<ConceptSummary> — list all concepts with member counts. pub fn should_split(concept, member_embeddings) -> bool — variance > SPLIT_THRESHOLD. pub fn should_merge(concept_a, concept_b) -> bool — cosine(centroid_a, centroid_b) > MERGE_THRESHOLD. (3) Concept name generation: top 3 TF-IDF keywords from member observation texts. Concept description: template '{N} observations about {keywords} across {entities}'. Both update on membership change. (4) Concept centroid update: when observation joins concept, new_centroid = (old_centroid * (N-1) + new_embedding) / N. O(dim) per update. ACCEPTANCE: (A) find_nearest_concept returns None on empty store. (B) After 3 similar observations, crystallize_concepts produces 1 concept. (C) Concept entity has all 6 schema attributes. (D) Observation entities have :exploration/concept Ref to their concept. (E) should_split detects when concept covers diverse topics. (F) concept_inventory lists concepts sorted by member count descending. (G) Concept names are human-readable (top keywords, not IDs). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/concept.rs (new), crates/braid-kernel/src/schema.rs, crates/braid-kernel/src/lib.rs. DEPENDS-ON: CCE-1 (embedding infrastructure). TRACES-TO: ADR-FOUNDATION-014 (Convergence Thesis — concepts close the ontology loop)."
